review:
I've never been a fan of retro-style games, but I've been introduced to it with Octopath Traveler, that I loved. So I thought I'd give Chasm a try. And here I am, after more than 15 hours playing it. I'm not familiar with metro√Ødvanias, so I'm going to be down to earth:

    - The story is not captivating, but is enough to set up an environment to play with;
    - There's a wide variety of enemies making combat really entertaining, espacially when discovering new zones;
    - Music;
    - Characters are sweet.

Good environment;
Great soundtrack;
Nice combat;
A bit dull in regards to it's "magic" options;
Overall, a must-have Metroidvania.

