Ok, now that i finished the game i will write another review.

Chasm is a good game, is not great, is not bad. If you are a fan of Metroidvania, buy it. If you just like Metroidvania, there is better games for the same price, wait for a sale then buy Chasm.

Pros:

-The art is great;
-There is a great variaty of enemies;
-It's a metrodivania with elements of RPG, and for those who are fans, we don't see much of this games around;
-The dev is reading the forum and is listening, so there is a great chance that he will fix the cons and the game will became a lot better.

Cons:

-The dev need to solve the evade system, i beat the game without using the evade button not even once, because it's just sucks, there is this weird delay between attacks, and the evade don't cancel any action, so it's just better run than trying to get the right time to use the evade;
-The story is kind of meh... There is no deepnes in the characters, nothing that hooked me up to carry about;
-I did not liked the "no hit" system. In this game if you kill the bosses without taking any hit you will receive a secret item (weapon, armor, etc.) But the thing is, that you spend more time restarting the game and walking around to the boss room, than actually fighting. I did every bosses whithout taking hit, but i did not enjoyed and din't feelt rewarded.

What i really missed:

In my opnion the dev putted so much efforte in the artwork of the game (which looks amazing) but din't put any customization for our charater, for me one of the biggest aspect of getting a new armor is to see how badass you look wearing it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Long story short, after i bypassed the fact that i would not use the evade at all, i really enjoyed the game, at the beggining your char is so bad that is soo frustrating when you touch a drill troll and die, but things get better in the mid game and forward.
